<TITLE> Bus strike called off in 8 southern districts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)  An "indefinite' bus strike that began in eight southern districts from Monday morning was called off in six of the districts by Khulna-Barisal divisional bus owners and workers association the same afternoon. The strike was called off at around 4 pm with buses running on different routes after from 4.30pm, said president of Bagerhat inter-district road transport association Sheikh Nazrul Islam. "It was called off in Barisal after a meeting with the administrative officials at the office of Barisal divisional commission. We too called our srike off following that," he said. The bus owners and workers association called the strike to meet their four-point demands including withdrawing cases filed against their members by BRTC for vandalising a BRTC bus and beating up the driver at Kochua in Morelganj, Bagerhat, in July. Running BRTC buses in the southern routes according to previous agreements and banning nasimon, karimon and rented motorbikes on the highways are the other demands. The eight southern districts which faced the bus strike from Monday morning were Bagerhat, Khulna, Pirojpur, Jhalkathi, Barisal, Bhola, Patuakhali and Barguna. There were no buses running district routes and long-distance inter-district buses, including to and from Dhaka, also remained off the road up to 4:30 pm. bdnews24.co
